    fix(client): remove server-side config import and use basepath from Zustand
    
    Fix a runtime error caused by accessing server-side environment variables in client components by removing imports of the config library and reading basepath from the existing Zustand store (useStore). This ensures client code uses client-safe state for image URLs and avoids server-only globals.
    
    - Remove config imports from client components
    - Replace config.prefix with basepath from Zustand (useStore)
    - LoginBody.tsx reads basepath from store and applies to login background
    - Signup page uses basepath from Zustand
    - No breaking changes; aligns client code with server-only config usage

